<TEXT>
sothebys auction house announced wednesday that 
it will buy the contents of a manhattan gallery for 1428 million 
in what may be the biggest art deal ever both because of the 
number of paintings and their value 
sothebys will acquire one of the great inventories of 
20thcentury art when it buys the 2300 works from the pierre 
matisse gallery in a joint venture with william acquavella a new 
york art dealer 
until now sothebys has represented art sellers putting up for 
auction works owned by others and taking a commission from the sale 
with the acquisition of the matisse gallery works sothebys 
will be in the business of owning the art it sells rather than 
operating in the auction houses traditional manner of representing 
sellers 
acquavella will be managing partner of the joint venture company 
being set up with sothebys to be called acquavella modern art 
as far as i know it is the biggest art deal both in the 
number of paintings and the art value that has been done in the art 
world acquavella told the new york times 
the gallerys inventory of 2300 works by artists including joan 
miro alberto giacometti and marc chagall is being sold by the 
estate of pierre matisse an art dealer and son of painter henri 
matisse pierre matisse died aug 9 
some of the artworks will be sold at auction but acquavella 
said he also planned to have exhibitions around the world and work 
with dealers in different countries to sell the works privately 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

