<TEXT>
hundreds of contra rebels outside 
this mountain hamlet refused to begin handing over their weapons 
wednesday the day the antisandinista guerrillas were to start 
demobilizing 
two hours after violeta barrios de chamorro was sworn in as 
president about 500 rebels gathered on a hillside in one of five 
security zones where the demobilization is to take place 
israel galeano a top rebel chief and 12 other contra 
commanders were on hand galeano delivered an antisandinista 
diatribe and vowed he would be the last to lay down his weapon 
then he invited his men to surrender their arms 
the guerrillas broke out in laughter en masse nobody gives up 
his gun shouted one and all cheered 
galeano known as commander franklin addressed the troops after 
meeting briefly with spanish maj jose luis gracia representative 
of the united nations central american peacekeeping force 
gracia said the un contingent was ready to begin accepting the 
rebels weapons the peacekeepers however have no mandate to 
forcibly disarm the contras 
the incident occurred in zone 1 a security enclave 85 miles 
north of managua that covers 174 square miles 
while it is not the largest of the five zones geographically it 
is thought to harbor the most fighters about 3000 contras are 
estimated to have arrived the past week 
about 9000 contras are to gather in the five zones in coming 
days 
the rebels who roam the zone at will are unsupervised and have 
sovietmade assault rifles grenade launchers and other weaponry 
they have small stores of food and are supposed to receive 
demobilization aid from the organization of american states 
the assembled rebels were also addressed wednesday by roberto 
ferrey who traveled to the zone to represent mrs chamorro 
now it is the turn of the resistance to take action 
contributing to peace and reconciliation he said you have to 
make an effort to understand that the sandinistas are no longer in 
power 
he appealed for demobilization before june 10 the date agreed 
to in a pact signed last week by oscar sobalvarro the no 2 man in 
the contra command 
several contras though rose to challenge ferrey 
jackson a regional commander told assembly id rather 
take to the mountains live in the jungle with my comrades until 
our conditions are met and those conditions have not yet been 
met 
of the dozens interviewed at the assembly not a single contra 
said he would hand over his weapon as long as the sandinistas 
controlled the army and security forces 
mrs chamorro named gen humberto ortega former president 
daniel ortegas brother to head the army as a conciliatory 
measure she is commander in chief 
</TEXT>
