<TEXT>
roman catholic bishop leo t maher who drew 
widespread attention when he banned a prochoice political 
candidate from receiving communion last year underwent surgery to 
remove a brain tumor wednesday 
maher 74 was in serious condition after the 2hour operation 
at scripps clinic in la jolla doctors said they were optimistic he 
would recover from the surgery but expressed concern about a 
recurrence of the lifethreatening tumor 
dr thomas waltz who led the operating team said doctors 
removed 75 percent to 80 percent of the tumor which was about 3 
inches in diameter and located in the back right portion of the 
brain 
its a tumor that you really cant classify as either 
malignant or benign waltz said it doesnt spread to other 
parts of the body but it can recur 
he said the tumors possible recurrence can be suppressed by 
radiation therapy 
maher checked into the clinic monday after his physician became 
concerned over his condition the diocese of san diego said in a 
statement tests then revealed the brain lesion and the surgery was 
scheduled said sue pondrom a spokeswoman for scripps clinic 
in the past several weeks the diocese said maher has grown 
increasingly aware of a lack of physical strength and at times has 
demonstrated a loss of equilibrium 
at midday pondrom confirmed that the operation had been 
completed but said no information on the bishops condition would 
be released until later in the day 
scores of catholics started a prayer vigil for the bishop on 
tuesday 
under diocesan law maher must retire as head of the 
460000member diocese by his 75th birthday july 1 
he has held the position since 1969 his tenure has been marked 
by great growth in the diocese as well as by controversy most 
recently he last fall banned lucy killea then an assemblywoman 
running for state senate from receiving communion because of her 
outspoken views in favor of abortion rights 
the sanction and its implications on the abortion issue and the 
separation of church and state became focal points for voters who 
elected killea a democrat over republican carol bentley 
bentley a prolife candidate blamed mahers intervention and 
the subsequent national publicity killea received for her loss in 
the republicandominated district 
</TEXT>
