<TEXT>
in what appeared a drugrelated mob hit 
masked gunmen killed five people and wounded seven as they opened 
fire inside a coffee bar and at occupants of a car parked outside 
authorities said 
tuesdays slaughter was carried out in the style of the camorra 
a crime syndicate that is a rough equivalent of the sicilian mafia 
said investigating magistrate paolo albano 
he said it appeared the killings were part of battles over the 
flourishing illegal drug trade in the area 
the attack occurred in the early hours in the hamlet of 
pescopago about 20 miles north of naples 
the dead included two tanzanians one iranian and one italian 
police said they could not immediately identify the other dead 
among the wounded was the 13yearold son of the coffee bars 
owner 
doctors operating on one of the wounded a 23yearold 
tanzanian found 10 bags filled with heroin in his stomach the 
italian news agency ansa reported 
there are africans who sell drugs here and the massacre is 
either directed towards the africans who are operating on their own 
or towards africans whom the camorra supplies with drugs albano 
said 
