<TEXT>
some people might think that fussing over a name 
is much ado about nothing but those people arent named 
shakespeare 
of those who are about 115 turned up to celebrate the bards 
birthday tuesday at the site of the new globe theater it was the 
largest gathering of shakespeares since 1964 which was celebrated 
as the playwrights 400th birthday all seemed proud of their 
illustrious name 
of course it may be that none of the latterday shakespeares is 
related to englands premier playwright genealogies are hazy on 
this point 
but never mind 
we all like to think were related to the bard said stanley 
shakespeare a london hairdresser who pored through phonebooks for 
six months to compile the invitation list of 600 shakespeares 
throughout britain 
hes not picky invitations went to people named shakespear 
shakspear shaxper and other variations 
those who came to london will be guests of honor at a week of 
readings dinner parties films and concerts organized by the 
friends of shakespeares globe but for most of the shakespeares 
the important thing was being together as a family 
these shakespeares are all fantastic really friendly and we 
all feel a natural empathy with each other even though most of us 
have never met before said 33yearold phil shakespeare a 
supermarket manager in west bromsgrove near stratforduponavon 
the playwrights birthplace 
he munched on a piece of fried chicken and chatted briefly with 
a new acquaintance 35yearold rosamund shakespeare who carried 
10monthold hillary shakespeare on her hip 
ms shakespeare said she kept her maiden name and passed it to 
her daughter because i think it sounds nicer than my husbands 
name kukowski 
besides she added she has always been fascinated by the 
playwright and as a teenager hitchhiked with her brother to 
stratforduponavon arriving long after dark 
we couldnt find a room and slept on the steps of the royal 
shakespeare theater i thought it so ironic that the shakespeares 
couldnt find a bed for the night in stratford 
the next day i put a rose on williams grave she said 
the shakespeares donned yellow hardhats and visited the 
construction site where a replica is being built of the elizabethan 
globe theater the playhouse most closely associated with the bard 
a 30foothigh banner bearing shakespeares portrait was 
unfurled next door on the new midland bank building also under 
construction 
gangs of workers stopped drilling and hammering to listen to a 
few lines from henry v then gordon schwontkowski of cary ill 
told the shakespeares how he handpainted the huge banner at night 
in his high school gym as a donation to the theater project 
the banner will hang at the worksite until the globe opens in 
1993 
last year archaeologists uncovered the original theater about 
300 yards from the new site on the south bank of the thames after 
lunch the shakespeare clan visited the site 
carl shakespeare lingered behind to enter his name in the 
guestbook alongside the signatures of stanley shakespeare beryl 
shakespeare dorothy shakespeare and the rest 
the 25yearold research chemist said he never felt any impulse 
to write although he was capable of turning a pretty phrase 
when i was 13 i wrote a descriptive story about the wind 
which my teacher said was the best she had ever read she read it 
aloud to the class and i must admit it was pretty good said 
shakespeare who paused a moment to reflect 
who knows he said maybe theres a budding shakespeare in 
all of us 
