<TEXT>
a fledgling ohio politician is coming clean 
less than two weeks before a congressional primary election in 
hopes that voters will like a candidate who tells the truth about 
telling a lie 
ricky lee mattox a democrat who wants to oust republican rep 
donald buz lukens confessed to using a masquerade to get 
lukens to explain the secrets of his past successes 
using another name and posing as a college student researching a 
paper on political strategy mattox asked lukens to map out the 
tactics he used to win election and reelection 
lukens obliged 
although embroiled in the worst political mess of his 
20plusyear career the congressman met with his wouldbe rival at 
a restaurant in middletown ohio in february and described how to 
win in the 8th district 
what he said was i would never tell one of my opponents 
this but mattox said from oxford ohio he confided in me 
tactics about his first and second campaigns that i thought were 
brilliant 
i came out of the meeting with a lot of respect for him the 
28yearold mattox said ive never met anyone with as much 
political knowledge 
lukens said tuesday that he remembered meeting mattox he 
seemed receptive he seemed like a nice guy the incumbent said 
i am a little surprised that ricky would go to that extent 
lukens said if he had just told me he was ricky mattox i would 
have given the same advice 
but would he have gone into the same stepbystep detail 
oh sure replied lukens theres no secret about it 
theres nothing magic the key is timing and application 
lukens then detailed how he goes about working the district 
beginning with tiny farm towns and ending in the cities 
his description matched exactly mattoxs inventory of lukens 
campaign tactics it also matched secondhand accounts of lukens 
own activities as he struggles for his political life while 
uncertain of the outcome of his appeal for a sexrelated 
misdemeanor involving a teenage girl 
lukens has been highly visible in his district making the 
rounds of serviceclub breakfasts farm group meetings and other 
small gatherings 
lukens has steered clear of republican meetings and candidate 
forums since his official stance is that hes waiting for the 10th 
ohio district court of appeals to settle the challenge of his 
conviction for contributing to the unruliness of a minor 
mattox hasnt followed lukens advice 
lukens advocates steering clear of areas where opponents are 
strong and concentrating instead on where the ducks are mattox 
spent a lot of time going doortodoor in hamilton ohio the 
hometown of his chief democratic rival gregory jolivette 
lukens told mattox that a year of advance work was a basic 
