new york metropolitan area and probably was turning out 2 million 
of the plastic halfinch vials a day 
four or five times weve found machinery but nothing close to 
this scale said customs agent victoria ovis 
three people were arrested under a state law passed last summer 
against producing drug paraphernalia customs officials also said 
they seized three plastic molding machines and hundreds of 
thousands of vials 
the owner of the building was not identified police said 
crack vials previously were imported from southeast asia and 
labeled as perfume containers on shipping manifests 
but since 1987 when a federal law outlawing imports of drug 
paraphernalia went into effect domestic production of the 
containers has increased the new york times reported today 
making packages for illegal drugs is estimated to be a 1 
billionayear industry 
