lawmakers are criticizing the defense 
department for removing the director of its high technology 
research agency 
members of congress said the defense advanced research projects 
agency is the only place in government where tax dollars are used 
to promote cuttingedge technology that can help make us 
businesses more competitive overseas 
the pentagon said craig fields who headed darpa for a year was 
transferred rather than fired from the agency but his supporters 
in industry and in congress contended fields was removed last 
friday for emphasizing dualuse technology which has civilian as 
well as military applications 
this is the triumph of ideology over the national interest 
said house majority leader richard gephardt dmo 
gephardt referred to conservatives in the administration who 
argue that government should refrain from investing in nondefense 
research from which private industry would profit they say the 
free market should be allowed to work and that industry should 
finance its own research 
gephardt was among 11 lawmakers of both parties who signed a 
letter tuesday urging the defense department to reinstate fields to 
his post at darpa he also asked the house armed services committee 
to investigate the situation 
the research agency has a 12 billion budget about half of 
which goes to dualuse technologies rep mel levine dcalif 
said at a news conference 
darpafunded projects include super computers artificial 
intelligence software semiconductor manufacturing technology and 
biotechnology levine whose home state is a hightechnology 
center is cochairman of the congressional hightechnology caucus 
levine also chairs rebuild america a publicpolicy group that 
promotes hightechnology industries he said he is drafting 
legislation that would put darpa under control of the commerce 
department and require that funds be spent only on dualuse 
technology except in special cases 
sen john heinz rpa who signed the letter said he does not 
want president bush to go down in history as the president who 
presided over the economic decline of the united states of america 
