a car bomb exploded today near a truck 
carrying antiterrorist policemen in the city of medellin killing 
five officers and wounding five the defense ministry said 
an unspecified number of civilians were killed or injured and 
the roofs of several nearby buildings collapsed the caracol radio 
network reported 
no one immediately claimed responsibility for the attack 
however the medellin drug cartel one of the nations largest 
has pledged to kill police officers as part of its terrorist 
campaign aimed at forcing the government to halt its efforts to 
crack down on the cocaine trade 
the police officers belonged to a special antiterrorist unit 
sent to medellin to fight drug traffickers a communique issued by 
the ministry said 
the car bomb exploded as the truck was taking the officers to 
their posts in the city 160 miles northwest of bogota 
it was the second major car bomb attack this month aimed at 
police in medellin a drugtrafficking center 
caracol said that several bodies could be seen lying in the 
street in the citys commercial district after the bomb exploded 
today it said the dead included workers in a nearby shoe store 
the explosion caused the roofs of the shoe store and several 
small factories in the area to collapse a caracol reporter on the 
scene said he added that the blast destroyed several vehicles 
on april 11 a car bomb containing nearly 500 pounds of dynamite 
exploded on a busy highway in the city killing 20 people 
including eight police officers from the antiterrorist police unit 
police blamed the medellin cartel and its leader pablo escobar 
for the explosion but no claim of responsibility was received 
after that blast police sent 300 additional members of the 
antiterrorist unit to join the search for escobar and those 
responsible for the bomb attack 
