union must allow lithuanians to exercise selfdetermination 
but baker told a senate appropriations subcommittee in 
washington that the bush administration still was not prepared to 
impose economic sanctions on moscow to force negotiations with 
lithuanian leaders 
the soviet union forcibly annexed lithuania in 1940 along with 
the other two baltic states latvia and estonia 
a lithuanian delegation remained in moscow today trying for a 
second day to meet with kremlin officials but the republics 
representation in the soviet capital said no meetings had been set 
as of this morning 
