tours in various parts of the country to get a sense of public 
opinion 
sverdlovsk residents have taken to the streets several times 
over the past months including a prenew years protest over a 
shortage of vodka 
party officials stopped the protests by flooding the stores with 
reserves of vodka but many of the citys 14 million residents 
remain unhappy about the lack of other rationed items including 
meat sugar and butter the soviet press has reported 
sverdlovsk is also one of several russian centers where 
communist party members recently ousted their local chief and 
