here are excerpts from recent editorials in newspapers 
throughout the country 
april 24 
the clarionledger jackson miss on hostages 
the release of robert polhill is welcome news and the united 
states should encourage terrorist groups to release the 10 
including seven americans still held captive 
but the west cannot condone any reciprocal moves as iran 
requests without condoning hostagetaking 
at worst polhills release is a cynical terrorist bet that the 
political advantage of holding hostages is waning they are trying 
to eke what they can with these human beings they view as mere 
bargaining chips 
at best they are showing an unlikely change of heart 
in any case the bush administrations stand of no deals 
appears to be working and should remain intact 
it may appear hardhearted to show no response to what is being 
touted as a humanitarian gesture by iran in calling for release 
of polhill and at least one more hostage 
but that hardheartedness pales beside the barbarism of 
kidnapping 
to show reconciliation toward polhills tormentors would only 
make the west an afterthefact accomplice to that crime 
the road polhill took to damascus and freedom was long we hope 
fervently that the road will be cleared for the remaining captives 
but we cannot reward cruelty cloaked as magnanimity 
