april 19 
birmingham ala postherald on ralph david abernathy 
it was the rev ralph david abernathys fate to live most of 
his adult life in the shadow of a friend who became a legendary 
figure in the civil rights movement and us history dr martin 
luther king jr 
it was not easy to be in succession the friend of and 
collaborator with such a man as he embarked on the course that 
would change a country and bring international fame the mans 
chief aide as success and fame grew and finally with assassination 
enhancing the legend the designated successor who did not have the 
extremely rare talents found in king 
abernathy who died april 17 at age 64 paid a price for not 
being all that others in the civil rights movement thought kings 
successor should be in 1977 he was pressured to resign as 
president of the southern christian leadership conference which he 
had helped king to create in the following years he became 
increasingly alienated from and criticized by other civil rights 
leaders climaxed last fall by widespread denunciations because of 
what he wrote about kings sex life in his autobiography 
but the most important period in abernathys life and the 
period for which he should be remembered was from montgomery 
ala in the mid1950s to memphis tenn in 1968 this 
country is a better place because of what ralph david abernathy did 
during those years 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

