<TEXT>
four months after a bloody revolution 
toppled the communist dictatorship an atmosphere of fear and 
violence remains fed by the peoples suspicion that holdouts from 
the ceausescu regime will stay in power 
the interim leadership includes many former communist officials 
and some romanians claim there is a deliberate attempt to keep 
communism alive albeit in a less stringent form 
the reluctance in purging the bureaucracy of nicolae ceausescu 
loyalists has fueled a hysterical distrust among people here who 
suffered like nobody else in the soviet bloc under the harsh 
