<TEXT>
dexter gordon revered by jazz fans as a 
pioneering tenor saxophonist and known to filmgoers for his 
oscarnominated performance in the 1986 movie round midnight 
died today he was 67 
gordon died at 1250 am of kidney failure said don lucoff 
spokesman for blue note records in new york he said gordon had 
been in poor health and was admitted to thomas jefferson university 
hospital in philadelphia on march 18 for treatment of cancer of the 
larynx 
nevertheless gordon recently had finished filming 
awakenings a movie with robert deniro and robin williams 
its very very difficult to even contemplate that weve lost 
such a great master of his instrument and icredible human being 
said guitarist george benson he was quite a man 
in the 1940s gordon helped define the bebop style of jazz begun 
by lester young charlie parker and john coltrane and his playing 
influenced future generations of musicians 
critics hailed his combination of youngs melodic approach with 
the harddriving sound and complex harmonics of coleman hawkins and 
parker 
gordon born in los angeles began his career with the big bands 
of america including those of lionel hampton louis armstrong and 
billy eckstine 
he fell on hard times in the 1950s as bebop fell from favor and 
served a twoyear prison sentence in california in 1962 he moved 
to paris and spent the next 14 years as part of the expatriate jazz 
scene that inspired round midnight 
in 1960 he acted in a play the connection and began a 
series of albums on the blue note label that reestablished his 
reputation and brought his sound to a new generation of fans 
the movie about an aging fading saxophonist in a paris club 
whose health and career are revived by a young french fan was 
largely based on the life of pianist bud powell but had many 
parallels with gordons life 
gordon raspy voiced worldweary his 6foot5 frame tottering 
from the ravages of drugs and drink was a compelling figure in 
the film and he received widespread acclaim 
it was the first time in academy award history that a musician 
was nominated for the bestactor oscar 
he managed to record five albums for blue note between 196165 
the most outstanding dexter gordon with its cross section of 
styles dont explain demonstrated his moody range on ballads 
gordons other records include long tall dexter savoy 
our man in paris go homecoming and swinging affair 
dexter gordon swiss nights true blue more than you 
know dexter quartet i found a new baby long tall 
dexter 1946 the chase 1947 doin alright 1961 dexter calling 
a swingin affair one flight up our man in paris 1963 
homecoming 1976 
a memorial was planned for may 6 in new york lucoff said 
