<TEXT>
soviets and americans met again by 
the river elbe on wednesday marveling at the imminent unity of 
germany exactly 45 years after they helped cut it in two 
under gray skies and a light drizzle about 100 world war ii 
veterans watched a solemn ceremony as a wreath was laid in the 
grassy river delta where the armies of two invading nations came 
together 
soviet and us veterans wearing medals from the historic 
military campaign clasped hands embraced and traded war stories in 
the first elbe reunion held on free german soil 
both armies invaded torgau as they drove through germany from 
opposite ends formally linking up april 25 1945 
william robertson 66 was credited with leading one of two us 
army scout patrols that made the first contact with the soviet 
forces 
to us veterans its a very big deal but it probably isnt to 
most americans said the retired physician from culver city 
calif 
but the elbe meeting touches something very deep in the hearts 
of the soviets he added 
the last such reunion was in 1985 and drew about 25000 people 
it was orchestrated by the soviets and the thencommunist east 
german government the united states criticized it as a propaganda 
extravaganza 
the gathering wednesday was more lowkey and attracted a crowd 
of only about 2000 people to the river bank on the edge of this 
aging town 75 miles southeast of berlin 
veterans marveled at the peaceful revolt that ousted east 
germanys hardline government the popular uprising opened the way 
for democratic government and eventual unification with west 
germany 
