regulatory commission should not be allowed to continue working on 
the nuclear weapons program 
department spokesman tom olson said stellos responsibilities 
would include overseeing the restart of nuclear material production 
at the savannah river reactors in south carolina 
retaining stello to manage these critical tasks sends a 
message that despite all the fine rhetoric the fundamental 
priorities of the doe have not changed schwartz said 
in a joint statement sen samm nunn dga chairman of the 
armed services committee and sen john warner rva ranking 
republican on the panel said bush had formally withdrawn the 
nomination and that the matter was closed 
energy secretary james d watkins who urged the committee to 
confirm stello last fall has made no public comment on the 
withdrawal 
