his effort to resolve problems with junkbond debt at another of 
his companies community newspapers inc 
ingersoll offered to buy back at cutrate prices more than half 
of the companys 240 million in junk bonds which it used for 
expansion but no bondholders signed up to sell their bonds back to 
ingersoll even though the bonds have been trading at an even lower 
price about 40 cents on the dollar than what he offered 
if the company cant agree with bondholders on a buyback it 
could be forced to more than double the interest rate on some of 
the bonds this june to a rate of more than 26 percent 
ingersoll said those problems were unrelated to the sun 
