britains merchandise trade deficit soared in 
march to 36 billion the secondworst gap on record the 
government reported wednesday 
the widening from 23 billion in february sent the pound 
plummeting and prompted the bank of england to intervene to support 
the british currency 
the government blamed the shortfall largely on higher imports of 
oil and of erratic items such as civil aircraft and precious 
