<TEXT>
florida has ordered aerial pesticide spraying to 
protect the states 14 billion citrus industry from an 
infestation of medflies 
spraying of malathion has worked in past infestations of the 
mediterranean fruit fly and theres no reason to change methods now 
and run into the grave risk of getting into the predicament 
california is in state agriculture commissioner doyle conner 
said tuesday 
in southern california aerial spraying of malathion in suburban 
neighborhoods has caused an uproar while the pest has spread into 
orange and grapefruit groves in some of the regions richest 
farmland 
and while expanded spraying over a 52squaremile area of los 
angeles and san bernardino counties was ordered tuesday scientists 
admitted that malathion spraying there may be a failing strategy 
its clear that were not doing the job with the current 
approach said jim carey an entomology professor at the 
university of california davis and member of the state medfly 
science advisory board the medfly infestation is bordering on 
being out of control if not out of control 
the first florida spraying against medflies begins thursday in a 
16squaremile zone covering areas northwest of downtown miami and 
near miami international airport thats where six of the pests 
have been found since april 16 
three other sprayings will follow over the next several weeks 
after four weeks millions of sterile medflies will be released to 
break the breeding cycle 
the last medfly infestation in south florida was in 1987 when 
five males were found the states last major outbreak affecting 
commercial groves spread across 28 counties in 1956 
environmentalists in california and here have objected to use of 
malathion contending too little is known about the chemicals 
longterm health effects 
the bad thing about using these kinds of chemicals is that 
they wipe out all of the insects in an area the good and the 
bad said lee emerson a member of the sierra club its not 
the kind of balanced environmentally sensitive approach we should 
be taking these days 
joette lorion a miami coordinator of earth day said if its 
a danger to your car and theyre asking you to wipe it off it must 
be a danger to your body 
the mixture of malathion and syrupy bait can damage car paint if 
not rinsed off quickly 
officials also said that people with health problems such as 
asthma or allergies may want to remain indoors during the 
spraying but conner said of malathion it has not been 
determined anywhere to be a health risk 
medflies could strike a harsh blow to floridas citrus industry 
which was crippled by a christmas freeze medfly larvae hatch 
inside more than 250 varieties of fruits and vegetables turning 
them into mush 
bobby mckown executive vice president of florida citrus mutual 
in lakeland said monday the 12000member growers organization 
supports immediate action to control and eradicate the medflies 
so they dont expand beyond residential areas 
the pesticide to be sprayed per acre consists of 24 ounces of 
malathion mixed with sticky bait malathion is used in a stronger 
concentration of 31 ounces per acre throughout florida for 
mosquito control 
