people are eating cereal more than bacon and eggs and danish 
and bagels said analyst roger spencer of painewebber inc 
chicagobased sara lee reported net income of 1089 million or 
44 cents a share for the three months ended march 31 compared with 
95 million or 40 cents a share for the same period a year ago 
sales for the quarter fell 13 percent to 28 billion from 
284 billion reflecting both the disposition of some of sara 
lees foodservice businesses at the beginning of fiscal 1990 and a 
9 percent drop in bakery unit volume after a 10 percent increase in 
last years comparable quarter sara lee said in a statement 
unit volume refers to the amount of product shipped as opposed 
to revenue which refers to the dollars received from the sale of 
goods 
