ranged between 15880 yen and 15915 yen during morning trading 
traders attributed the nikkeis setback to declines in stock 
index futures prices that discouraged market players 
haruhito ichimura a trader with nippon kangyo kakumaru 
securities co said many investors were reluctant to buy issues 
ahead of the golden week holidays that start saturday and go 
through may 6 for many japanese companies 
they are trying to stay on the safer side especially due to 
uncertainties over foreign exchange fluctuations he said 
in currency dealings the dollars strength followed its 
overnight upswing in new york dealers said 
the dollar gained ground as market players bought the west 
german mark against the yen which indirectly helped weaken the yen 
against the dollar said toru kanai a foreign exchange analyst 
with new japan securities co buying and selling was evenly matched 
when the dollar crossed the 159yen level he added 
trading was thin ahead of the golden week holidays kanai 
said 
masaaki tanahashi a dealer with mitsui taiyo kobe bank said 
holidays that shut markets in australia and new zealand wednesday 
kept trading very light 
